    "title": "Guix: build riscv64 master / v30rc1 fails",
    "body": "### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behaviour\n\nWhile building a guix-build of v30rc1 or main for `riscv64-linux-gnu` architecture fails with : \n\n```console\n[100%] Linking CXX executable ../../bin/test_bitcoin\nriscv64-linux-gnu-ld: CMakeFiles test_bitcoin.dir/main.cpp.o: in function \"boost::fpe::disable(unsigned int)':\nbitcoin depends/riscv64-linux-gnu/include/boost/test/impl/execution_monitor.ipp:1538: warning: fedisableexcept is not implemented and will always fail \nriscv64-linux-gnu-ld: CMakeFiles/test_bitcoin.dir/main.cpp.o: in function 'boost::fpe: :enablefunsigned int)':\n/bitcoin/depends/riscv64-linux-gnu/include/boost/test/impl/execution_monitor.ipp:1502: warning: feenableexcept is not implemented and will always fail\n[100%] Built target test_bitcoin make: \n*** [Makefile: 146: alll] Error 2\n```\n\nbuilding tag version 29.0 / 29.1 / 29.2rc1 works , other architectures also build as expected. \n\nBuilding on aarch64 nixos 25.05 / M1 max \n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nSuccessful build \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\n```shell\ngit clone https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin.git -b v30.0rc1 --depth 1\ncd bitcoin\nenv HOST='riscv64-linux-gnu' ./contrib/guix/guix-build\n```\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```console\n[100%] Linking CXX executable ../../bin/test_bitcoin\nriscv64-linux-gnu-ld: CMakeFiles test_bitcoin.dir/main.cpp.o: in function \"boost::fpe::disable(unsigned int)':\nbitcoin depends/riscv64-linux-gnu/include/boost/test/impl/execution_monitor.ipp:1538: warning: fedisableexcept is not implemented and will always fail \nriscv64-linux-gnu-ld: CMakeFiles/test_bitcoin.dir/main.cpp.o: in function 'boost::fpe: :enablefunsigned int)':\n/bitcoin/depends/riscv64-linux-gnu/include/boost/test/impl/execution_monitor.ipp:1502: warning: feenableexcept is not implemented and will always fail\n[100%] Built target test_bitcoin make: \n*** [Makefile: 146: alll] Error 2\n```\n\n\n\n### How did you obtain Bitcoin Core\n\nCompiled from source\n\n### What version of Bitcoin Core are you using?\n\nv30.0rc1\n\n### Operating system and version\n\nNixos 25.05 \n\n### Machine specifications\n\napple m1 max ",
